  "why": "The paper provides partial diagnostic insight into failures by (1) reasoning about the optimization landscape (noting the non-convexity of spatial transformation space and why gradient-based search fails) and (2) linking augmentation-selection to model internals via alternate fitness/selection metrics (loss-based vs. neuron-coverage and loss-based vs. classification-based point-wise robustness). However, it does not present diagnostic analyses that explain underlying model vulnerabilities in terms of learned/spurious features, dataset bias, or class-level failure concentration (no confusion-matrix/classwise failure analysis or attribution of failures to specific non-robust features). Thus the evidence is limited to internals/statistical selection metrics rather than root-cause explanations.",
